==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nuclein
<hw>Nu"cle*in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A constituent of the nuclei of all cells, containing
protein and nucleic acid. It is a colorless amorphous substance, readily
soluble in alkaline fluids and especially characterized by its
comparatively large content of phosphorus. It also contains nitrogen and
sulphur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nucleobranch</ent>⟦br⟧
